Recommends: xwayland
Description: Native Linux soundboard with virtual microphone support
 A high-performance, native Linux soundboard built with Rust, GTK4, and
 Libadwaita. Features include:
  * Virtual microphone for routing audio to Discord, OBS, Zoom, etc.
  * Mic passthrough to mix your voice with soundboard audio
  * LUFS normalization for consistent volume levels
  * Native Wayland hotkeys via host-installed swhkd with full native X11/XWayland support
  * Modern GTK4/Libadwaita UI with dark mode support
  * PipeWire/PulseAudio integration
